text: More than a third of Covid-19 deaths had diabetes.
Significantly more people died of Covid-19 in two months than died of overdoses all of last year or the year before.
Just 2.9% of deaths were caused by Covid-19 in the first three months of 2020.

While the media talks a lot of the 150,000 deaths, perhaps they should have been talking about the number of people who died 'of Covid' not 'with Covid'. That was just 17,371 up to the end of quarter three 2021

text: More people died of suicide in 2020 than died of COVID-19.
